description: "Odd Man Out": The girls are sick of Jughead mooching off the food at their parties, so they tell him he's not invited unless he brings a date! If you know Jughead, you know why that's the worst news ever! Archie goes looking for a date for him, but can he find someone before Jughead makes a drastic decision?

"Obey That Impulse": Mr. Weatherbee is disappointed with the student body's lateness, until he gets an idea from teacher's pet Dilton that gets the students to be more proactive. But this psychology trick isn't just bringing out the good impulses in people -- it's bringing out the bad ones, too!

"Kiss Me Again": Veronica and Archie have both found their way to Betty's house, and are too busy fawning over each other to pay attention to Betty! She manages to get Archie to help her fix a lightbulb, and steals a hair-raising kiss! You'll never believe the SHOCKING end to this tale!

"Very Kindly Yours": In an effort to show the staff of Riverdale High that they're appreciated, Betty and Veronica have organized a "Be Kind to Teachers" Week! The boys aren't convinced, but only because they're getting detention for harebrained stunts! When they have a change of heart, can they show the teachers that they really do want to turn over a new leaf?
"Some Enchanted Evening": Archie and Veronica are going on a double date -- with Jughead?! Who is the reluctant Romeo going to bring -- and could she have an appetite to match Jughead?

"Fine Feathered Friends": Veronica and Archie have built a beautiful birdhouse together, but they can't get anything to nest in it! When they finally come up with a solution, though, that birdbrain Jughead manages to mess everything up!
"Low-Down Highbrow": Archie is leaving town for a week, and that can only mean one thing -- Reggie's going to try his luck with Veroncia! Can Arch convince Jughead to keep her occupied all week?

Shock-Headed Peter's addictions start getting the better of him as he and Girl 2 begin a workplace romance. Elsewhere, Irma Geddon confronts her feelings about motherhood versus career as a jailbreak sends everyone at the police station into a panic.
name: All You People

description: "Board With It All": Archie and Jughead are sick and tired of having to stay after school every day to wash the blackboards, and it's cutting into Archie's dating time! The two come up with a plan to win Ms. Grundy's favor. Will they succeed before they have a chance to mess everything up?
"Call Me Mister!" It looks like Archie might finally be ready to start shaving! That's good for his ego, but not for his parents' -- their little boy is growing up fast!
Veronica hasn't been around all week--and it sounds like it's because she's found a new boyfriend! Can Archie keep his temper under control as he finds out who this mysterious new distraction is?
"By Shnook or Crook": Archie can't seem to keep other people's things out of his pockets! Could be a kleptomaniac, stealing things compulsively? Or is he just a forgetful goofball?

"Dish-orderly Conduct": How is Archie going to take Veronica to the movies tonight if he doesn't have any money? He'll have to find a way to earn some quick cash, or Reggie will be taking her instead!
"Winner Lose": When Reggie starts to hog Ronnie's attention with his new boat, Archie is determined to beat him in a boat race! Only one problem, though -- Archie doesn't HAVE a boat!

"Atomic Fishin'": Mr. Lodge is in a bad mood because he can't seem to catch any fish. That's why it's called fishing and not catching, Lodge ol' boy! But don't worry, Archie has a plan to build your confidence again! You'll get hooked on this hilarious story and many others!
"To Have and To Hold!": Betty wants to be a little more lovey-dovey with Archie, but all he's interested in is the television! Can Jughead's age-old gag trick him into Betty's arms?

"Clucky Buck": The newspaper is running a special contest -- match the serial number on a dollar bill to a number they print in the paper and win $100! Sounds like it's too good to be true -- until it happens!

"Card Sharps": If Archie gets a bad report card this week, his dad will keep him from going to Saturday's dance! Rotten ol' Reggie is out to sabotage him, though, so he can have Veronica all to himself! Will his dirty tricks pay off?

"Doing What Comes Naturally": Archie has been making plaster casts of people's heads, and Archie is determined to cast Mr. Lodge as well! But Lodge knows better by now, and he's prepared to turn the tables...
"From Rags to Crutches!": Moose has it out for Jughead! He's got a new beatdown technique he's eager to try out. But the way he explains it might be just as bad as being on the receiving end of it!
"Backfield in Emotion": Football season is upon us, and that means fewer dates for everyone! But can the boys find a way off the team without getting blacklisted by the coach and Mr. Weatherbee?

As the Skaven chitter ominously around the tattered Empire army, Greatsword Frohlich finally wrestles answers from the Necromancer Brecht. The reason behind the Clan Skyre scurrying forth with their foul warpstone engines is revealed! There are worse things than Skaven abroad in the Empire!
name: Chapter IV

description: 'The blue-garbed man of mystery known as The Angel plummeted like a stone out of the blazing firestorm! Death on the street below appeared to be his only destination! 'But suddenly, with a titanic effort, he managed to twist his red cape against the wind! Itself flickering with flame, the glider sent his muscular form hurtling through the windows of an office building's upper stories with a teeth-rattling crash...'

The wheels of fate have been set in motion as the Dominion swears vengeance for the destruction of the royal skyship Artemis. As fallen comrades are being given a final farewell, brothers torn by tragedy are forced to choose sides. Witness as one is hailed as the grandest hero of the Dominion while the other swears forever revenge. Meanwhile, not all is well in the darkened alleys of the Dominion's capital city, as forces darker than any imaginable must be fed in human currency.

Don't miss the second blockbuster issue from fan favorites Stephen Platt (Wolverine/Cable, Prophet, Moonknight) and Christian Lichtner (Battlechasers, X-Men, Rising Stars, Darkness/Batman) as they take you on their epic journey.

True power rears its ugly head as Aries is thrown into the midst of deadly intrigue and cold ambition. Even as the Dominion is celebrating him as their latest champion, plans are underway for retribution against the wayward Khan Hordes for the treacherous destruction of the royal skyship Artemis. The secret of the prophecy is discovered by an unlikely figure and true motivations become apparent as we finally are given a glimpse of who is actually at the helm of the Dominion. Meanwhile, dark forces are plotting within the inner bowels of the Dominion and we soon discover that not all is what it seems.

See what all the buzz is about and don't miss the third installment of the epic saga from fan favorites Stephen Platt (Wolverine/Cable, Prophet, Moonknight) and Christian Lichtner (Battlechasers, X-Men, Rising Stars,

The Dominion finally strikes back against the Khan! Bloody retribution supplants failed diplomacy as Aries finds himself part of the elite squadron chosen to capture the Khan chief responsible for the destrution of the Artemis. However, his first mission leads him to question the values he's held dear all his life. Meanwhile, Lord Draken is ordered to find the bearer of the mark by any means necessary while feline ambition shows itself in cold calculation...

Don't miss this installment of the epic saga from fan favorites Stephen Platt (Wolverine/Cable, Prophet, Moonknight) and Christian Lichtner (Rising Stars, Darkness/Batman, Battlechasers, X-Men).

Aries is horrified at the atrocities he is forced to witness during a brutal campaign of retribution in the frontier. As he struggles to face his inner turmoil, he finds himself charged with the capital crime of high treason. At the same time alarm and disillusionment ripple throughout the empire, as Lord Draken consorts with his true masters over the path of their sinister design. Meanwhile Aries awaits his fate in the imperial prison, as he is confronted with shocking revelations that will have far reaching implications throughout the entire course of this epic tale.

Don't miss this next gripping installment of the epic saga from sizzling hot creators Stephen Platt (Wolverine/Cable, Prophet, Moonknight) and Christian Lichtner (RISING STARS, BATMAN/DARKNESS, Battlechasers, X-Men,).

In the fourth and final issue of Bartholomew of the Scissors, the White Blob, bent on assimilating the human race, rises from the sea to secure its stronghold on the town. In a desperate battle, Gordon Watt enlists the help of the National Guard to drive the monstrous organism back into the sea. Meanwhile, Jessica and Victor fall into the clutches of a witch-hunting mob seeking the annihilation of all Spectral Phantasms. Only Bartholomew of the Scissors and his menacing Scissor Swarm has the power to save them from being burned alive at the stake.
Begins reprinting of Legion of Super-heroes Volume 3
name: Here A Villain, There A Villain...

volume.name: Tales of the Legion of Super-Heroes
Tales of the Legion of Super-Heroes
Tales of the Legion of Super-Heroes

description: As Johann faces the fight of his life, Abe and Kate learn the story of Victorian occultist Martin Gilfryd's transformation into Memnan Saa, the prophesied king of Hyporborea who would 'tame fire to breed dragons.' Written by Mike Mignola and John Arcudi, and drawn by Guy Davis, B.P.R.D.: The Black Goddess follows The Warning as part two of a trilogy that pulls together threads from the beginning of the series-and leaving the B.P.R.D. and the world forever changed.

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: Hell comes to North Point as the remorseless Irons siblings spread unbridled violence and their monstrous curse to the helpless town folk. When the moon ascends over the burning scar that was a border town, the innocent victims rise again as creatures of the night, laying in wait for the pursuing gunfighter determined to end the curse. This year's biggest supernatural western tale continues and no one is safe from the coming storm.

Every student at Midtown High knows that Flash Thompson is numero uno at every game he plays...and that rule applies to more than just varsity sports. Flash's video gaming skills are the stuff of legend, and they just got him noticed by a super-villain looking to test a brand new arcade machine -- one that could destroy all of New York City! Will Peter Parker be able to swing into action and save his high school arch-nemeis before it's too late...or will this finally be 'game over' for the spectacular Spider-Man?! Insert 12 quarters to find out...
name: Playing Hero

description: A PENNY SHORT IS A DAY SAVED: In a time long gone, the Ancient One fought a tremendous battle against the Dread Dormammu, ultimately banishing the ruler of the Dark Dimension back to his own reality by power of a mystically binding contract. Unfortunately for Dr. Strange, that mystical contract is hundreds of pages long, and the Dread One has now found himself one nasty lawyer, and a whole lot of loopholes. Dr. Strange is going to need all the mystical might he possesses, along with the legal prowess of one Mr. Foggy Nelson, Attorney At Law, in order to send Dormammu packing, or maybe just to stay alive!
name: Contractual Discombobulations

description: The rival school to ps238, Praetorian Academy, has challenged the students of ps238 to a soccer game! When it's discovered by an intrepid few that the goal of the game is to make ps238 look unworthy of parent and public support, it's up to Tyler and his friends to figure out how to turn the tide of public opinion, if not win the game! The only problem is who Praetorian Academy's Headmaster has sent to keep things from going awry!
name: Super Soccer

description: After alien invasions, incursions into our world by the supernatural, and choices about the future of superheroes, it's back to schoolwork for the kids of ps238. Miss Kyle has assigned a creative writing assignment, and we get to read along. What insights into the budding superhero mind will we see? And is Zodon using this exercise to drop hints about his next evil scheme?

The forces of Order and Chaos - who suspiciously resemble angels and demons - are wreaking havoc in Wonderburg, and it may be up to Malphast to stop it. As the offspring of both order and chaos, he might have a hidden ability to save the world or doom it to eternal struggle between good and evil. And will Tyler's clone have a part to play in all of this?
name: Malaphast and the Mysterious "Meh!"

description: Tyler Marlocke has always been a boy with no powers, going to school alongside the children of Earth's mightiest. Has he finally gained the abilities his parents have yearned for him to have? Can he control them without unraveling the universe? And will the planet survive a showdown between the Lords of Order and Chaos?
name: Quantum Powers

description: Trapped in an altered reality that is 'off 'bout a quarter-turn to the left,' the members of RFC's 5th Squadron are scattered across war-torn Europe facing personal crises, seemingly insurmountable challenges, and the viscous otherworldly elemental creatures. The only way out is to find each other and somehow get back to the world they know. But that's easier said than done! What is it they say about frying pans and fire?

volume.name: Ray Harryhausen Presents: War Of The Elementals

1. Wail of a Tail!

2. Fashion Emergency! 
 
It's a frighteningly fashionable issue! The Mystery Inc. gang investigates a haunted beauty pageant by the sea, and chases a ghost through the catacombs of Paris!
name: Wail of a Tail!
